#### Description

I am writing an application that monitors the resources variation of the system. I need to get a JSON file and later on use the data to plot a graph. I am using the following command

`glances --export json --export-json-file ./"my directory" --disable-plugin percpu,memswap,network,diskio,fs,docker,sensors,ip,uptime`

I am exporting the JSON with only the data that matters to me.

The problem is that the exported JSON has a wrong format; The JSON is missing the "[  ]" and the commas that separates the extracted objects.

Example:
```
--> This "[" is missing (added manually) 
[
  {
    "cpu": {
      "total": 25.7,
      "user": 22.9,
      "system": 2.5,
             .... 
    },
    "load": {
      "min1": 1.3,
      "min5": 2.12,
          .....
    },
    "mem": {
      "total": 33639563264,
          .....
    },
    "network": {},
    "fs": {},
    "processcount": {
      "total": 314,
           ....
    },
    "system": {
      "os_name": "Linux",
              ....
    },
    "sensors": {},
    "gpu": {
      "0.key": "gpu_id",
           ....
    }
  },   The "," is also added manually
  {
    "cpu": {
      "total": 25.8,
      "user": 16.4,
      "system": 2.0,
           ....
    },
    "load": {
      "min1": 1.28,
      "min5": 2.1,
          ....
    },
    "mem": {
      "total": 33639563264,
      "available": 27626160128,
                ...
    },
    "network": {},
    "fs": {},
    "processcount": {
      "total": 314,
           ....
    },
    "system": {
      "os_name": "Linux",
                 ....
    },
    "sensors": {},
    "gpu": {
      "0.key": "gpu_id",
      "0.gpu_id": 0,
           ....
    }
  }
]
```

Glances v3.1.6.2 with PsUtil v5.8.0.

Is there any other way to extract JSON data with the right format?

The format needed is the following:

```
[
{"First Data Fetch"},
{"Second Data Fetch"},
{"Third Data Fetch"},
.....
{"N Data Fetch"}
]
```

#### Description

Exporting net data to influxdb seems to fail after starting too many docker containers. I'm not sure exactly when the failure happens but I currently have 16 containers running and glances has stopped logging net data.

I'm using the following query in grafana:

``` sql
SELECT mean("enp0s25.rx")/mean("enp0s25.time_since_update")*8 AS "down", mean("enp0s25.tx")/mean("enp0s25.time_since_update")*8 AS "up" FROM "network" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
```
#### Versions
- Glances (glances -V): 2.6.2
- PSutil (glances -V): 4.3.0
- Operating System (lsb_release -a): Fedora 23
